 (footballer)|Kim Sung-Nam]]\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Award Winners ===\n\n* R League MVP Award Winners \n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-left:center;\" \n|-\n!#\n!Year\n!Player\n!Position\n!Notes\n|-\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|1\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|[[2002 R-League|2002]]\n|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Park Dong-Suk]]\n|[[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|2\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|[[2004 K-League|2004]]\n|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Han Dong-Won]]\n|[[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n* R League Top Scorer Award Winners\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-left:center;\" \n|-\n!#\n!Year\n!Player\n!Position\n!Goals\n!Matches\n!Goals per Match\n!Notes\n|-\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|1\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|[[1990 R-League|1990]]\n|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Kim Dong-Hae]]\n|[[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]]\n|<CENTER>7</center>\n|<CENTER>?</center>\n|\n|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|2\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|[[2000 R-League|2000]]\n|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Wang Jung-Hyun]]\n|[[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|<CENTER>8</center>\n|<CENTER>8</center>\n|<CENTER>1.00</center>\n|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|3\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee\"|[[2005 K-League|2005]]\n|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Han Dong-Won]]\n|[[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|<CENTER>10</center>\n|<CENTER>20</center>\n|<CENTER>0.50</center>\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== FC Seoul Academy == \n=== History ===\nFC Seoul didn't had practical [[youth system]] by 2006. In 2007, FC Seoul affiliated with Dongbuk High School FC as U-18 team.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=107&oid=001&aid=0001534727|script-title=ko:\ud504\ub85c\ucd95\uad6c FC \uc11c\uc6b8, \uba85\ubb38 \ub3d9\ubd81\uace0 \ucd95\uad6c\ubd80 \uc9c1\uc811 \uc6b4\uc601|publisher=[[Yonhap News]]|date=2007-01-31|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012 December, FC Seoul established U-18 team and U-15 team at Osan Schools.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://m.fcseoul.com/mobile/news_tv/fcnews_view.jsp?seq=2846&tcd=news&pg=12|script-title=ko:FC\uc11c\uc6b8, \uc624\uc0b0\ud559\uc6d0\uacfc U-18, U-16, U-14 \ucd95\uad6c\ud300 \ud611\uc57d\uccb4\uacb0|publisher=FC Seoul.com|date=2012-08-28|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014 December, FC Seoul established U-12 Team. FC Seoul constructed [[youth system]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sports.news.naver.com/general/news/read.nhn?oid=277&aid=0003409585|script-title=ko:'FC\uc11c\uc6b8\uc758 \ubbf8\ub798' U-12\ud300, \ucc3d\ub2e8 \uccab \uc804\uc9c0\ud6c8\ub828|publisher=FC Seoul.com|date=2015-01-08|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n=== Coaching staff ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Position\n! Name\n! Notes\n|-\n| U-18 Team Manager\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Cha Du-ri]]\n|\n|-\n| U-18 Team Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Kim Jin-kyu]]\n|\n|-\n| U-18 Team Goalkeeping Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Weon Jong-teok]]\n|\n|-\n| U-18 Team Fitness Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Hwang Ji-hwan]]\n|\n|-\n| U-15 Team Manager\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Kim Young-jin (footballer)|Kim Young-jin]]\n|\n|-\n| U-15 Team Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Park Hyuk-soon]]\n|\n|-\n| U-15 Team Goalkeeping Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Son Il-pyo]]\n|\n|-\n| U-15 Team Fitness Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Jung Hoon-gi]]\n|\n|-\n| U-12 Team Manager\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Kim Byung-chae]]\n|\n|-\n| U-12 Team Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Seo Ki-man]]\n|\n|-\n| U-12 Team Goalkeeping Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} [[Lee Ji-hun]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n=== FC Seoul U-18 Team ===\n{{further information|ko:\uc624\uc0b0\uace0\ub4f1\ud559\uad50 (\uc11c\uc6b8) \ucd95\uad6c\ubd80}}\n\nFC Seoul U-18 Team is Osan High School FC in Seoul. Osan High School FC is founded on December 2012.\nFrom 2007 to 2012, FC Seoul U-18 Team was Dongbuk High School FC.\n\n==== Honours ====\n* '''K League Junior'''\n** Winners (1) : 2009\n* '''Korea High School Football Championship (Spring)'''\n** Winners (1) : 2019\n\n==== Statistics ====\n* 2008-2012 seasons were Dongbuk High School FC period.\n\n===== K League Junior - Season by Season Records =====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Season\n! Teams\n! Final<br />Position\n! Group<br />Teams\n! Group<br />Position\n! {{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n! {{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n! {{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n! {{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n! {{Tooltip| GF | Goals For}}\n! {{Tooltip| GA | Goals Against}}\n! {{Tooltip| GD | Goal Difference}}\n! {{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n! Knockout<br />Stage\n! Manager\n|-\n|2008\n|8\n|3rd\n|4\n|Group A<br />2nd\n|12\n|9\n|1\n|2\n|32\n|12\n|align=right|+20\n|28\n|3rd\n|align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Choi Jin-Han]]\n|-\n|2009\n|13\n|bgcolor=gold|'''Champions'''\n|6\n|Group A<br />1st\n|15\n|12\n|2\n|1\n|36\n|10\n|align=right|+26\n|38\n|bgcolor=gold|'''Champions'''\n|align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Choi Jin-Han]]\n|-\n|2010\n|14\n|3rd\n|7\n|Group A<br />2nd\n|12\n|6\n|1\n|5\n|21\n|17\n|align=right|+4\n|19\n|3rd\n|align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Lee Young-Ik]]\n|-\n|2011\n|14\n|11th\n|7\n|Group A<br />5th\n|18\n|5\n|7\n|6\n|25\n|24\n|align=right|+1\n|22\n|11th\n|align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Lee Young-Ik]]\n|-\n|2012\n|16\n|Group A<br />5th\n|7\n|Group A<br />5th\n|22\n|10\n|6\n|6\n|42\n|30\n|align=right|+12\n|36\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Not held\n|align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Lee Young-Ik]]\n|-\n|2013\n|17\n|9th\n|colspan=\"2\"|'''Single round robin system'''\n|16\n|7\n|2\n|7\n|29\n|21\n|align=right|+8\n|23\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Kike Linero]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===== K League Junior - Knockout Stage Records =====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Season\n! Teams\n! Position\n! {{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n! {{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n! {{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n! {{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n! {{Tooltip| GF | Goals For}}\n! {{Tooltip| GA | Goals Against}}\n! {{Tooltip| GD | Goal Difference}}\n! [[Penalty shootout (association football)|PSO]]\n! Manager\n|-\n|2008\n|4\n|3rd\n|1\n|0\n|1\n|1\n|0\n|1\n|align=right|-1\n|N/A\n|align=left|{{flagicon|K