(FOS) Program the Youth Football Academy to find promising young players for the future and also planning and involving in Social Contribution Events to enhance the football infrastructure and environment. \n\nOutstanding players in Future of FC Seoul can transfer to U-12 team.\n\n==== Notable graduate ====\n* {{flagicon|KOR}} [[Ju Se-jong]], {{flagicon|KOR}} [[Ahn Hyeon-beom]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[FC Seoul]]\n* [[R League]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.fcseoul.com/ FC Seoul Official Website] {{in lang|ko|en}}\n* [http://academy.fcseoul.com/main.asp Future of FC Seoul Official Website] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/fcseoulyouth Future of FC Seoul Official Facebook]  {{in lang|ko}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170415004523/http://blog.naver.com/fcseoulyouth Future of FC Seoul Official Blog] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://www.kleague.com/KOR_2016/junior/schedule.asp K League Junior Fixtures and Results] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://blog.naver.com/withkleague K League Junior Official Blog] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://www.joinkfa.com/ Nation Youth Football League Fixtures and Results] {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{FC Seoul}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fc Seoul Academy}}\n[[Category:FC Seoul|Y2]]\n[[Category:K League academies|Seoul]]\n[[Category:Reserve team football in South Korea|Seoul]]\n", "text_old": "'''FC Seoul Reserves''' are the [[reserve team]] of [[FC Seoul]]. Reserve team is member of the [[R League]] (Reserve League). \n\n'''FC Seoul Academy''' is the [[youth system]] of [[FC Seoul]].  The academy consists of U-18 Team, U-15 Team, U-12 Team and Future of FC Seoul. The Future of Seoul U-12, U-15, and U-18 are considered to be academy while the rest are for young players playing as a hobby. U-18 Team is a member of the K League Junior (Youth League).\n\n== FC Seoul Reserves ==\n=== History ===\nFC Seoul Reserves was built in 1990 for first [[R League]]. But [[R League]] existed just for one year. \n\nIn 2000, [[R League]] relaunched, and FC Seoul Reserves was rebuilt for competition.\nThere are many players played for reserves including [[Lee Chung-Yong]], [[Song Jin-Hyung]], [[Ko Myong-Jin]], [[Ahn Sang-Hyun]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sports.media.daum.net/general/news/moresports/breaking/view.html?cateid=1076&newsid=20041112033637827&p=ilgansports|script-title=ko:1\uad70 \ud5a5\ud574 \uc3dc\ub2e4 - \uafc8\uc775\ub294 \uc5f4\uc5ec\ub35f \uc18c\ub144|publisher=Daily Sports |date=2004-11-12|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n=== Coaching staff ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Position\n! Name\n! Notes\n|-\n| Reserve Team Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} \n|\n|-\n| Reserve Team Goalkeeping Coach\n| {{Flagicon|KOR}} \n|\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Honours ===\n* '''[[R League]]'''\n** '''{{Gold1}} Winners (3)''': [[2000 R-League|2000]], [[2002 R-League|2002]], [[2004 R-League|2004]]\n** {{Silver2}} Runners-up (2): [[2001 R-League|2001]], [[2005 K-League|2005]]\n\n=== Statistics ===\n==== R League - Season by Season Records ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size:100%;\"\n! Season\n! Teams\n! Final<BR/>Position\n! Group<BR/>Teams\n! Group<BR/>Position\n! {{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n! {{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n! {{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n! {{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n! {{Tooltip| GF | Goals For}}\n! {{Tooltip| GA | Goals Against}}\n! {{Tooltip| GD | Goal Difference}}\n! {{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n! Knockout<BR/>Stage\n! Manager\n|-\n|[[1990 R-League|1990]]\n|5\n|4th\n|N/A\n|N/A\n|12\n|4\n|3\n|5\n|18\n|20\n|align=right|-2\n|11\n|N/A\n|align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Jung Hae-Seong]]\n|-\n|[[2000 R-League|2000]]\n|9\n|bgcolor=gold|'''Champions'''\n|5\n|Central League<BR/>1st\n|16\n|8\n|4\n|4\n|32\n|22\n|align=right|+10\n|28\n|bgcolor=gold|'''Champions'''\n|rowspan=\"3\" align=left|{{flagicon|KOR}} [[Shin Jae-Heum]]\n|-\n|[[2001 R-League|2001]]\n|10\n|bgcolor=silver|'''Runners-up'''\n|5\n|Central League<BR/>2nd\n|16\n|9\n|1\n|6\n|31\n|29\n|align=right|+2\n|28\n|bgcolor=silver|'''Runners-up'''\n|-\n|[[2002 R-Lea